1
00:00:06,006 --> 00:00:07,757
- [jolly music playing]
<i>- Hey, everyone!</i>

2
00:00:07,841 --> 00:00:09,426
<i>Can you guess what this summer is?</i>

3
00:00:09,509 --> 00:00:13,096
<i>Yeah! It's the children's expo! Hooray!</i>

4
00:00:13,888 --> 00:00:15,765
<i>Now, come on! Follow me.</i>

5
00:00:15,849 --> 00:00:17,475
<i>Let's have an adventure!</i>

6
00:00:17,559 --> 00:00:21,021
<i>Welcome to the city of the future</i>
<i>in Yamanashi!</i>

7
00:00:21,521 --> 00:00:25,400
<i>If we all hold hands and work together,</i>
<i>a bright future awaits us all!</i>

8
00:00:25,483 --> 00:00:28,820
<i>- The World Children's Peace Exposition…</i>
- [man 1] Hey! Get the hell back!

9
00:00:28,903 --> 00:00:32,407
- Spit that out right now!
- [music becomes dramatic orchestral march]

10
00:00:32,490 --> 00:00:35,368
You think you can
just grab food off our plates? Huh?

11
00:00:35,452 --> 00:00:38,455
- [man 2] You're a sucker for punishment.
- [man 3] Hey, hold up!

12
00:00:38,538 --> 00:00:42,500
- [man 1] You think you can play with me?
- [man 2] I'll rip it out of your mouth!

13
00:00:43,626 --> 00:00:46,337
[announcement] <i>Make sure</i>
<i>to wipe off excess sweat and dirt</i>

14
00:00:46,421 --> 00:00:48,423
<i>before reentering the facility.</i>

15
00:00:48,506 --> 00:00:50,800
<i>Personal hygiene is</i>
<i>of the utmost importance,</i>

16
00:00:50,884 --> 00:00:53,344
<i>not only to you</i>
<i>but to others and the staff.</i>

17
00:00:53,428 --> 00:00:55,346
<i>So make sure to get cleaned up.</i>

18
00:00:55,430 --> 00:00:57,974
<i>If you do notice any changes</i>
<i>in your physical condition,</i>

19
00:00:58,058 --> 00:01:00,477
<i>please notify</i>
<i>a member of staff immediately.</i>

20
00:01:00,560 --> 00:01:03,897
- [music ends]
- [man grunting]

21
00:01:15,492 --> 00:01:16,367
Hey.

22
00:01:17,243 --> 00:01:20,163
- You see that shooting star the other day?
- [girl] Mm-hmm.

23
00:01:21,081 --> 00:01:22,332
You wish for anything?

24
00:01:23,458 --> 00:01:26,544
[woman] Why not? That's what you're
supposed to do with a shooting star.

25
00:01:26,628 --> 00:01:31,007
Well, I wished that I was rich enough
to never have to work again.

26
00:01:31,091 --> 00:01:32,425
- [banging]
- [man 2] You there!

27
00:01:33,510 --> 00:01:36,012
Stop fooling around
and get your ass back to work!

28
00:01:36,554 --> 00:01:38,973
Don't make me come in there.
I'll break your jaw!

29
00:01:41,059 --> 00:01:43,061
[gentle acoustic guitar music playing]

30
00:01:51,694 --> 00:01:54,322
[siren blaring]

31
00:01:59,285 --> 00:02:00,662
All right, everyone!

32
00:02:00,745 --> 00:02:05,083
We are recruiting additional workers
for an environmental cleanup project.

33
00:02:05,166 --> 00:02:09,003
The compensation for this will be
five times the standard rate.

34
00:02:09,587 --> 00:02:13,383
If you're interested in taking part,
then you should raise your hand.

35
00:02:13,466 --> 00:02:16,386
- I am!
- [woman 2] Over here, me! I'm interested!

36
00:02:16,469 --> 00:02:18,680
You don't want to? Let's do it together.

37
00:02:18,763 --> 00:02:20,723
- [man] Any other takers?
- [woman 2] Me!

38
00:02:20,807 --> 00:02:22,767
[man] The long-haired lady in 105!
You're in!

39
00:02:22,851 --> 00:02:24,644
- [people shouting]
- [man] Anybody else?

40
00:02:24,727 --> 00:02:27,856
Okay, you, the bald guy in 204.
I have you down.

41
00:02:27,939 --> 00:02:29,983
- Anyone else?
- [woman 2] I need the money!

42
00:02:30,567 --> 00:02:31,401
Huh.

43
00:02:31,484 --> 00:02:33,278
The woman and kid in 303.

44
00:02:33,361 --> 00:02:35,029
Thank you. Okay, who else we got?

45
00:02:35,113 --> 00:02:37,949
Great! You see that?
My shooting star wish came true!

46
00:02:38,032 --> 00:02:41,494
[man] Okay, you, the woman
with the short hair. Perfect.

47
00:02:41,578 --> 00:02:44,414
Oh, and the man right below her.
We've got you down.

48
00:02:44,497 --> 00:02:45,790
Yes, ma'am, I see you.

49
00:02:45,874 --> 00:02:47,834
Is that it? No one else?

50
00:02:50,545 --> 00:02:52,088
[music fades out]

51
00:02:55,008 --> 00:02:57,969
WHITE CENTER

52
00:02:59,304 --> 00:03:01,389
[truck rumbling outside]

53
00:03:01,472 --> 00:03:03,558
[resident snoring]

54
00:03:03,641 --> 00:03:05,685
[resident sleep-talking]

55
00:03:09,772 --> 00:03:11,107
[snoring continues]

56
00:03:22,702 --> 00:03:24,704
[mysterious music droning]

57
00:03:43,014 --> 00:03:44,098
[latch clicks]

58
00:03:52,941 --> 00:03:55,568
- What are you gonna do?
- What do you think? Bury them!

59
00:03:55,652 --> 00:03:58,029
What, right here?
Are you serious? We can't do that.

60
00:03:58,112 --> 00:04:01,157
- What other choice do we have, huh?
- It's just that, uh…

61
00:04:01,658 --> 00:04:04,244
The meteorite is way too dangerous.

62
00:04:04,786 --> 00:04:06,329
Let's cut ties right now. Maybe--

63
00:04:06,412 --> 00:04:07,538
Just shut up!

64
00:04:07,622 --> 00:04:10,625
No one'll give a shit
if these people disappear anyway! Come on!

65
00:04:10,708 --> 00:04:14,254
- Hey, Satsuki! How'd it go?
- [Obata] Let's call the police…

66
00:04:14,337 --> 00:04:16,839
- Did you make a lot of money?
- [man] How stupid are you?

67
00:04:16,923 --> 00:04:19,592
If we go to the police,
we're back at square one!

68
00:04:19,676 --> 00:04:20,802
Satsuki?

69
00:04:22,971 --> 00:04:26,516
- [Obata] Are they really all dead?
- [man] You can't tell by the smell?

70
00:04:28,726 --> 00:04:30,895
- [man] There's no other choice…
- Satsuki?

71
00:04:31,521 --> 00:04:33,147
[Obata] That's gonna take forever.

72
00:04:33,231 --> 00:04:36,693
[man] We probably shouldn't waste time
talking about it, should we?

73
00:04:37,902 --> 00:04:39,112
I'm taking the car out.

74
00:04:45,952 --> 00:04:47,203
[man breathes heavily]

75
00:04:47,287 --> 00:04:48,955
[Obata] The sun's coming up soon.

76
00:04:49,038 --> 00:04:50,540
You think I don't know that?!

77
00:04:52,875 --> 00:04:54,460
You gotta keep this closed.

78
00:05:03,261 --> 00:05:05,263
[mysterious music building]

79
00:05:28,202 --> 00:05:29,329
Satsuki.

80
00:05:29,412 --> 00:05:30,705
[music fades out]

81
00:05:30,788 --> 00:05:31,998
Satsuki!

82
00:05:32,999 --> 00:05:34,584
Satsuki, wake up!

83
00:05:49,766 --> 00:05:52,769
[singing erratically]

84
00:05:57,398 --> 00:05:58,691
- [brakes screech]
- Oh!

85
00:05:58,775 --> 00:06:01,778
- [people laughing]
- [woman 1] Don't be lame. We have time.

86
00:06:01,861 --> 00:06:03,154
Hey! Outta the way!

87
00:06:03,237 --> 00:06:06,240
[woman 1] Let's go to one more place!
You know you want to!

88
00:06:06,324 --> 00:06:10,078
- Who is this guy, in his big truck?
- [man 1] Where'd you get those glasses?

89
00:06:10,161 --> 00:06:12,288
- [driver grunts]
- [woman 1] Oh my God!

90
00:06:12,372 --> 00:06:14,916
Hey! Stop what you're doing!
Get off of him!

91
00:06:14,999 --> 00:06:16,793
[driver] Wanna step in front my car?

92
00:06:16,876 --> 00:06:19,420
[woman 2] Somebody help!
He's attacking our friend!

93
00:06:19,504 --> 00:06:21,214
Stop! You're gonna kill him!

94
00:06:21,297 --> 00:06:23,007
[man 2] Calm down! We're gonna go!

95
00:06:23,091 --> 00:06:25,968
- [driver] You wanna die?!
- [woman 2] I think he broke his nose!

96
00:06:26,052 --> 00:06:28,429
- [melancholy music playing]
- [indistinct chatter]

97
00:06:38,773 --> 00:06:40,817
[indistinct chatter and laughter]

98
00:06:42,860 --> 00:06:46,072
- [man] Let me see your bag. What you got?
- [woman] Get over here!

99
00:06:46,572 --> 00:06:48,574
[melancholy music continues]

100
00:07:08,719 --> 00:07:11,973
BUNKO RAMEN

101
00:07:12,056 --> 00:07:13,683
[music fades out]

102
00:07:14,267 --> 00:07:15,476
[person slurping]

103
00:07:15,560 --> 00:07:18,312
- [man] Two spicy pork ramens, table two.
- [woman] Got it.

104
00:07:18,813 --> 00:07:20,440
[customer slurping]

105
00:07:21,023 --> 00:07:22,400
[woman] Here, spicy pork ramen.

106
00:07:30,199 --> 00:07:32,785
[poignant music playing]

107
00:07:40,877 --> 00:07:43,296
BUNKO RAMEN AFTER A FESTIVAL
IS THE BEST!

108
00:07:43,379 --> 00:07:44,547
I LOVE YOU, MOM

109
00:07:44,630 --> 00:07:47,467
THE MISO RAMEN
AND SALT GREEN ONION RAMEN ARE SO TASTY

110
00:07:47,550 --> 00:07:50,803
Wow, amazing. You can feel the love.

111
00:07:51,679 --> 00:07:55,600
- [man] You wanna get a picture?
- Oh, no, no. I'm by myself, it's sad.

112
00:07:56,100 --> 00:07:59,937
- I'll be in the picture with you.
- That's worse. Your face is terrifying.

113
00:08:00,021 --> 00:08:01,355
- Sorry?
- [woman laughs]

114
00:08:01,439 --> 00:08:04,901
Shave that beard. It's intimidating.
I don't wanna be in a picture with that!

115
00:08:04,984 --> 00:08:07,737
He'll never shave the beard off.
It's a lost cause!

116
00:08:07,820 --> 00:08:09,197
- [customer] Excuse me.
- Yeah?

117
00:08:09,280 --> 00:08:11,616
- [customer] Another order of gyoza.
- You got it.

118
00:08:11,699 --> 00:08:14,327
[customer] Instead of white rice,
can I do fried rice?

119
00:08:14,410 --> 00:08:15,286
Fried rice, got it.

120
00:08:15,369 --> 00:08:19,040
[customer 2] Actually, boss,
I'll take a half order of fried rice too.

121
00:08:19,123 --> 00:08:20,666
[man] Two orders of fried rice.

122
00:08:22,001 --> 00:08:23,628
Ren, want your usual?

123
00:08:24,378 --> 00:08:25,713
Uh, yeah.

124
00:08:26,214 --> 00:08:27,715
I'll take two, actually.

125
00:08:28,633 --> 00:08:29,634
Really?

126
00:08:32,136 --> 00:08:33,179
[girl gasps]

127
00:08:33,262 --> 00:08:35,806
[Ren] Wait, it's okay!
Stop! J… Hang on a second.

128
00:08:36,599 --> 00:08:39,227
Wait, are you hungry? You want some food?

129
00:08:43,689 --> 00:08:44,690
Uh…

130
00:08:45,650 --> 00:08:46,567
Right?

131
00:08:48,528 --> 00:08:49,737
'Cause, uh,

132
00:08:50,238 --> 00:08:52,240
I ordered way too much.

133
00:08:52,949 --> 00:08:54,742
Maybe you can help me eat it?

134
00:08:55,243 --> 00:08:57,036
I'd really appreciate it.

135
00:09:00,498 --> 00:09:02,833
I saw you wandering around before.

136
00:09:02,917 --> 00:09:04,293
Everything okay?

137
00:09:08,339 --> 00:09:09,173
Huh.

138
00:09:09,715 --> 00:09:11,384
Look at that cool stone.

139
00:09:11,968 --> 00:09:12,843
[chuckles]

140
00:09:14,428 --> 00:09:16,055
So where'd you come from?

141
00:09:20,476 --> 00:09:21,394
Hmm.

142
00:09:22,270 --> 00:09:23,104
Oh.

143
00:09:24,897 --> 00:09:26,023
[chuckles]

144
00:09:26,107 --> 00:09:27,275
Look, you wanna see?

145
00:09:27,775 --> 00:09:28,776
It's cool.

146
00:09:29,360 --> 00:09:30,194
[chuckles]

147
00:09:30,278 --> 00:09:31,946
It's a rice ball!

148
00:09:34,073 --> 00:09:35,074
[chuckles]

149
00:09:35,157 --> 00:09:36,325
No, huh?

150
00:09:37,410 --> 00:09:38,411
[sighs]

151
00:09:39,912 --> 00:09:41,664
So, uh, want some ramen?

152
00:09:42,248 --> 00:09:43,291
It's up to you.

153
00:09:43,374 --> 00:09:45,418
We can pig out and chat? That'd be fun.

154
00:09:46,460 --> 00:09:48,921
Hey, Ren. Should I call the police?

155
00:09:49,422 --> 00:09:51,215
Oh, wait! Don't go!

156
00:09:51,757 --> 00:09:53,134
Wait, stop!

157
00:09:53,217 --> 00:09:54,844
Hang on a second, it's okay!

158
00:09:54,927 --> 00:09:56,554
Hey, calm down. It's all right.

159
00:09:57,096 --> 00:09:58,472
It's okay, don't worry.

160
00:09:58,973 --> 00:10:01,225
We're not gonna call the police,
all right?

161
00:10:03,269 --> 00:10:04,729
I promise.

162
00:10:10,109 --> 00:10:11,235
Uh…

163
00:10:13,237 --> 00:10:15,031
Uh, I'll make you a deal.

164
00:10:16,907 --> 00:10:20,286
Tell me where your home is,
and I'll help you get back there.

165
00:10:20,369 --> 00:10:22,496
You just gotta
eat some ramen with me first.

166
00:10:23,331 --> 00:10:24,332
Okay?

167
00:10:27,585 --> 00:10:29,045
It's really good!

168
00:10:29,545 --> 00:10:31,839
[man] Here we are,
miso ramen with butter and corn.

169
00:10:31,922 --> 00:10:33,799
[Ren] Oh, that looks delicious!

170
00:10:33,883 --> 00:10:36,052
- [man] Enjoy!
- Ah! Perfect! Thank you!

171
00:10:36,135 --> 00:10:37,511
[radio] <i>This is Chris Peppler.</i>

172
00:10:37,595 --> 00:10:39,513
<i>- You're listening to </i>Radical Paradise!
- It's on!

173
00:10:39,597 --> 00:10:42,433
[DJ] <i>So I don't know</i>
<i>what you've all been up to lately,</i>

174
00:10:42,516 --> 00:10:45,394
<i>but I was lucky enough</i>
<i>to go to Céline Dion's concert…</i>

175
00:10:45,478 --> 00:10:48,147
[Ren] Mmm. Mmm, mmm.

176
00:10:48,230 --> 00:10:50,316
What's wrong? Dig in.

177
00:10:50,399 --> 00:10:52,193
[DJ] <i>It almost looked</i>
<i>like the bow of a ship…</i>

178
00:10:52,276 --> 00:10:54,278
[Ren] Mmm, mmm. Mmm.

179
00:10:54,779 --> 00:10:56,280
[DJ] <i>But enough about my weekend.</i>

180
00:10:56,364 --> 00:10:59,867
<i>Without further ado, I say we dive into</i>
<i>the segment you all been waiting for,</i>

181
00:10:59,950 --> 00:11:02,453
<i>or at least,</i>
<i>the messages I get indicate that.</i>

182
00:11:02,536 --> 00:11:04,205
<i>It's "Please Make a Wish!"</i>

183
00:11:04,288 --> 00:11:08,417
<i>The theme we set up for the week was,</i>
<i>"A thank-you I could never say until now."</i>

184
00:11:08,501 --> 00:11:12,880
<i>All righty, so today's lucky listener</i>
<i>is from… drum roll, please… Tokyo!</i>

185
00:11:12,963 --> 00:11:16,175
<i>They go by the radio name</i>
<i>Miso Ramen Lover Bunko!</i>

186
00:11:16,258 --> 00:11:18,678
<i>Let's see what they've got to say, huh?</i>

187
00:11:18,761 --> 00:11:21,263
<i>- "Hey, Chris, my long-awaited thank-you…"</i>
- Oh! Oh!

188
00:11:21,347 --> 00:11:22,348
Oh my God!

189
00:11:22,431 --> 00:11:24,558
- [man] You wrote in?
- I send one in every week!

190
00:11:24,642 --> 00:11:26,686
[DJ] <i>"I found myself</i>
<i>on the verge of collapse</i>

191
00:11:26,769 --> 00:11:28,104
<i>in front of this ramen shop."</i>

192
00:11:28,187 --> 00:11:30,398
- <i>"The owner took pity on me."</i>
- This is my letter!

193
00:11:30,481 --> 00:11:33,567
[DJ] <i>"He gave me ramen on the house</i>
<i>and took care of me."</i>

194
00:11:33,651 --> 00:11:36,028
<i>"When I asked him</i>
<i>why he was being so generous,</i>

195
00:11:36,112 --> 00:11:38,030
<i>he told me that he was in a good mood</i>

196
00:11:38,114 --> 00:11:41,742
<i>because the song he requested on the radio</i>
<i>got played that day."</i>

197
00:11:41,826 --> 00:11:44,203
<i>"Something about that taste of that ramen</i>

198
00:11:44,286 --> 00:11:47,248
<i>combined with the particular song</i>
<i>spoke to me."</i>

199
00:11:47,331 --> 00:11:49,291
<i>"It's something I'll never forget."</i>

200
00:11:49,375 --> 00:11:52,420
<i>"I'd love to play that same song</i>
<i>for that generous owner…"</i>

201
00:11:52,503 --> 00:11:55,506
- That was great!
- [man] You didn't have to do that!

202
00:11:55,589 --> 00:11:57,466
[DJ] "<i>Thanks for writing in, Bunko."</i>

203
00:11:57,550 --> 00:12:01,262
<i>"Now, how about we honor his request</i>
<i>and play that song?"</i>

204
00:12:01,971 --> 00:12:04,432
["Ellie My Love"
by Southern All Stars playing]

205
00:12:05,391 --> 00:12:06,225
Hey.

206
00:12:06,976 --> 00:12:08,227
You know this song?

207
00:12:09,061 --> 00:12:11,230
I'd never had a request played
before that.

208
00:12:11,814 --> 00:12:13,524
I was really excited.

209
00:12:14,233 --> 00:12:16,861
And the song from back then
is the same one that's on right now,

210
00:12:16,944 --> 00:12:20,948
"Ellie My Love."
I never thought it would get picked today.

211
00:12:21,031 --> 00:12:22,241
[Ren laughs]

212
00:12:23,284 --> 00:12:25,202
You're our little good-luck charm,
I guess.

213
00:12:25,286 --> 00:12:26,662
<i>♪ My love ♪</i>

214
00:12:26,746 --> 00:12:30,082
<i>♪ So sweet… ♪</i>

215
00:12:30,958 --> 00:12:31,792
[girl] Mm.

216
00:12:32,376 --> 00:12:33,753
Mm. Hmm?

217
00:12:37,548 --> 00:12:39,091
Don't call me little.

218
00:12:39,967 --> 00:12:41,302
I'm Kyoko.

219
00:12:43,387 --> 00:12:44,472
Kyoko?

220
00:12:46,307 --> 00:12:47,433
Well, I'm Ren.

221
00:12:48,809 --> 00:12:50,686
But how 'bout you call me Uncle Ren?

222
00:12:52,980 --> 00:12:54,398
[boy] Hey, Mom! Mom!

223
00:12:54,482 --> 00:12:56,275
One of the goldfish isn't moving!

224
00:12:56,358 --> 00:12:57,943
[woman] What? Where? Which one?

225
00:12:58,027 --> 00:13:00,780
- Right there.
- Oh no. Yeah, he's dead.

226
00:13:06,994 --> 00:13:08,996
["Ellie My Love" continues]

227
00:13:14,168 --> 00:13:15,544
[Ren] All right.

228
00:13:15,628 --> 00:13:18,506
You're a <i>Radical Paradise </i>listener,
aren't you?

229
00:13:18,589 --> 00:13:20,174
We thank you for calling in

230
00:13:20,257 --> 00:13:22,676
and now invite you
to tell us what you want.

231
00:13:22,760 --> 00:13:24,678
Make a wish!

232
00:13:25,513 --> 00:13:27,056
<i>♪ Ellie ♪</i>

233
00:13:27,139 --> 00:13:28,682
♪ <i>My love ♪</i>

234
00:13:28,766 --> 00:13:31,894
<i>♪ So sweet… ♪</i>

235
00:13:36,816 --> 00:13:38,734
[Kyoko sobs softly]

236
00:13:38,818 --> 00:13:41,737
[wails]

237
00:13:44,031 --> 00:13:46,617
[Ren] Oh! No, no, no, no, no.
Wait, I'm sorry.

238
00:13:47,451 --> 00:13:49,578
- Whoa!
- [Kyoko continues wailing]

239
00:13:50,830 --> 00:13:52,915
[Ren] <i>Hey, look,</i>
<i>it's the stone from before.</i>

240
00:13:52,998 --> 00:13:56,794
It… it's like a little ball.
You know, like a rice ball! Look!

241
00:14:00,798 --> 00:14:03,634
[intriguing music playing]

242
00:14:14,311 --> 00:14:15,729
Wait, don't run! I'll pay you!

243
00:14:19,316 --> 00:14:20,693
Hey, come on.

244
00:14:23,946 --> 00:14:26,323
You're gonna wanna hear this, trust me.

245
00:14:34,915 --> 00:14:37,501
[dark, dramatic music playing]

246
00:15:13,954 --> 00:15:19,209
HUMAN VAPOR

247
00:15:22,630 --> 00:15:24,506
[suspenseful music playing]

248
00:15:25,966 --> 00:15:27,092
First victim.

249
00:15:33,432 --> 00:15:34,934
The second victim.

250
00:15:39,647 --> 00:15:42,900
This means someone on the force
could be the next target.

251
00:15:53,827 --> 00:15:55,746
So, Otomo's phone
that was recovered at the scene.

252
00:15:55,829 --> 00:15:56,830
[Kenji] What about it?

253
00:15:56,914 --> 00:16:00,250
Well, we were able to determine
that a video was sent from that phone

254
00:16:00,334 --> 00:16:02,670
and then deleted, after Otomo died.

255
00:16:02,753 --> 00:16:03,796
OWNER: SABURO OTOMO

256
00:16:03,879 --> 00:16:05,673
[Kenji sighs] That's interesting.

257
00:16:05,756 --> 00:16:07,633
[Michiko] Who do we think could've…

258
00:16:10,427 --> 00:16:12,179
It must've been Kyoko Kono.

259
00:16:15,724 --> 00:16:18,185
She was chasing him in the car, huh?

260
00:16:33,701 --> 00:16:36,870
[Kyoko] <i>This is the journal the Fujishiro</i>
<i>Syndicate ordered Otomo to steal</i>

261
00:16:36,954 --> 00:16:38,914
from someone involved with White Center.

262
00:16:39,456 --> 00:16:41,792
All the evidence
is written in those pages.

263
00:16:42,793 --> 00:16:44,044
Oh wow.

264
00:16:44,962 --> 00:16:46,797
DIED OF ILLNESS

265
00:16:46,880 --> 00:16:48,382
WHEREABOUTS UNKNOWN

266
00:16:49,049 --> 00:16:52,261
I don't understand, don't you already
have everything you need?

267
00:16:53,262 --> 00:16:55,472
- If you go public with the journal…
- No.

268
00:16:55,973 --> 00:16:58,642
The journal alone…
doesn't directly implicate

269
00:16:58,726 --> 00:17:01,770
whoever authorized the disposal
and cover-up of the meteorite.

270
00:17:01,854 --> 00:17:02,688
[Fujita] Eh?

271
00:17:11,613 --> 00:17:13,282
[Fujita] "February 25th."

272
00:17:13,365 --> 00:17:14,867
"Mufu came to White Center

273
00:17:14,950 --> 00:17:18,996
to check in on the progress
of the meteorite disposal."

274
00:17:19,079 --> 00:17:21,790
So seems like Mufu made them do it, then?

275
00:17:22,833 --> 00:17:24,334
Yeah, well, I looked into that.

276
00:17:24,835 --> 00:17:28,005
But I didn't get a hit on anyone
or anything named Mufu.

277
00:17:28,589 --> 00:17:31,133
It's probably… some kind of code name

278
00:17:31,216 --> 00:17:33,635
for an underground operation
that dealt with this.

279
00:17:33,719 --> 00:17:37,765
[Fujita] "Mufu, Otomo, Sakamoto, and Kai."

280
00:17:38,599 --> 00:17:41,143
Wait… Otomo, I know that name.

281
00:17:41,226 --> 00:17:43,645
Wasn't he the yakuza boss
the Human Vapor just killed?

282
00:17:43,729 --> 00:17:46,899
[Kyoko] Yeah, so we know him and Sakamoto.

283
00:17:46,982 --> 00:17:49,401
That just leaves Mufu
and whoever this Kai is.

284
00:17:55,657 --> 00:17:57,785
If I can expose this Kai person

285
00:17:58,327 --> 00:18:00,788
and bring Mufu to justice
for what they did,

286
00:18:02,372 --> 00:18:03,874
that'll be the end of it.

287
00:18:05,375 --> 00:18:08,253
I won't hurt anyone else,
and I'll turn myself in.

288
00:18:09,713 --> 00:18:13,175
That's why I'm hoping
that I can trust you both.

289
00:18:13,884 --> 00:18:15,302
Here's my proposal.

290
00:18:16,845 --> 00:18:19,598
I want you to forget
about everything you learned today.

291
00:18:20,516 --> 00:18:23,560
In return, I'll give you
twice the amount we agreed on before.

292
00:18:23,644 --> 00:18:25,854
So… two mil?

293
00:18:28,065 --> 00:18:29,900
You'll get the journal as well.

294
00:18:30,651 --> 00:18:33,487
Just hang on to it quietly
till I turn myself in.

295
00:18:34,029 --> 00:18:35,030
Then you can report it.

296
00:18:35,114 --> 00:18:36,949
- Um, are--
- [Kaho] Sorry, no deal.

297
00:18:40,285 --> 00:18:44,706
Because you wanna kill them all, right?

298
00:18:46,291 --> 00:18:49,545
I understand it's revenge,
but murder is still murder.

299
00:18:50,212 --> 00:18:53,132
If you want to expose people
for the atrocities they committed,

300
00:18:53,215 --> 00:18:54,633
then you should do that.

301
00:18:55,551 --> 00:18:56,969
They deserve it.

302
00:18:57,636 --> 00:19:01,056
You just gotta do it the right way.
Report them. Expose them.

303
00:19:05,853 --> 00:19:08,772
- So, suddenly you care?
- [Kaho] You can't sink to their level.

304
00:19:09,273 --> 00:19:12,276
And if you do kill someone again,
I don't care how guilty they are,

305
00:19:12,359 --> 00:19:14,653
I'll expose you
and everything you're doing.

306
00:19:16,947 --> 00:19:18,115
So what now?

307
00:19:22,703 --> 00:19:24,413
You gonna kill me for that?

308
00:19:28,292 --> 00:19:30,294
[pensive music playing]

309
00:19:38,385 --> 00:19:40,387
[pensive music continues]

310
00:19:45,100 --> 00:19:46,476
[sighs]

311
00:19:47,728 --> 00:19:50,230
SEND FAX

312
00:19:52,608 --> 00:19:55,402
SENT

313
00:20:02,701 --> 00:20:06,288
KILL MAMORU SAKAMOTO
THE MAN IN THE PHOTO

314
00:20:06,788 --> 00:20:07,789
CREATE AUDIO

315
00:20:14,546 --> 00:20:19,968
SEND

316
00:20:28,769 --> 00:20:31,146
[man] Sorry, miss? We're here.

317
00:20:31,230 --> 00:20:32,231
[Kyoko] Oh.

318
00:20:45,452 --> 00:20:46,453
Kenji.

319
00:20:49,206 --> 00:20:50,415
What's wrong?

320
00:20:53,377 --> 00:20:54,920
The data from the journal.

321
00:20:56,338 --> 00:20:57,547
You took it.

322
00:21:00,717 --> 00:21:04,012
What did it say? Tell me, Kyoko.

323
00:21:04,680 --> 00:21:07,516
I'm sure you guys got a good look at it
when you recovered it.

324
00:21:07,599 --> 00:21:09,518
[Kenji] You erased everything, didn't you?

325
00:21:09,601 --> 00:21:11,979
[Kyoko sighs] I don't know
what you're talking about.

326
00:21:12,479 --> 00:21:14,898
- [Kenji] What?
- Yeah, I got the data in the journal.

327
00:21:14,982 --> 00:21:16,858
But I didn't erase anything.

328
00:21:17,734 --> 00:21:19,903
[sighs] I already told you, Kenji.

329
00:21:19,987 --> 00:21:22,990
There must be someone working this
from inside the force.

330
00:21:23,073 --> 00:21:25,409
No one on my team would do that.

331
00:21:27,452 --> 00:21:28,495
[Kyoko sighs softly]

332
00:21:55,605 --> 00:21:56,648
[Kenji sighs]

333
00:21:57,524 --> 00:22:00,277
[Kyoko] I respect your confidence
in law enforcement,

334
00:22:00,360 --> 00:22:03,655
but the journal has Superintendent General
Sakamoto's name in it.

335
00:22:03,739 --> 00:22:05,115
Care to explain that?

336
00:22:15,083 --> 00:22:17,085
MUFU'S OTOMO, SAKAMOTO, AND KAI

337
00:22:17,169 --> 00:22:19,254
SABURO OTOMO
MAMORU SAKAMOTO

338
00:22:19,338 --> 00:22:20,922
KAI: NO DETAILS

339
00:22:23,091 --> 00:22:24,718
What would you have done?

340
00:22:26,887 --> 00:22:31,975
If you were me, Kenji, would you share it,
knowing you'd be handing it to the enemy?

341
00:22:33,560 --> 00:22:34,603
Or maybe…

342
00:22:36,021 --> 00:22:39,608
you would meet with him,
and find out what Mufu is.

343
00:22:42,652 --> 00:22:45,739
[Sakamoto] <i>The opportunity to prove</i>
<i>you want nothing to do with her.</i>

344
00:22:46,239 --> 00:22:47,949
<i>That you're over the whole thing.</i>

345
00:22:48,658 --> 00:22:49,910
You're welcome.

346
00:23:03,924 --> 00:23:05,634
[Fujita, on video] <i>We found him.</i>

347
00:23:08,220 --> 00:23:09,679
[Kaho] <i>Is that the Human Vapor?</i>

348
00:23:10,180 --> 00:23:12,432
[Fujita] <i>It must be him. Just look.</i>

349
00:23:13,016 --> 00:23:14,184
<i>His face…</i>

350
00:23:15,894 --> 00:23:16,978
[puffs slowly]

351
00:23:17,062 --> 00:23:18,772
<i>We found him.</i>

352
00:23:19,272 --> 00:23:20,857
[Kaho] <i>Is that the Human Vapor?</i>

353
00:23:21,525 --> 00:23:23,819
[Fujita] <i>It must be him. Just look.</i>

354
00:23:24,319 --> 00:23:25,529
[Kaho sighs]

355
00:23:25,612 --> 00:23:26,530
[Fujita] <i>His face…</i>

356
00:23:27,572 --> 00:23:28,615
Kaho.

357
00:23:29,366 --> 00:23:31,118
<i>We found him.</i>

358
00:23:32,285 --> 00:23:35,205
We might never get
another opportunity like this.

359
00:23:35,872 --> 00:23:38,417
- Maybe we get in touch with her.
- [Kaho] I won't do it.

360
00:23:39,042 --> 00:23:41,169
Come on. Why not? [sighs]

361
00:23:42,087 --> 00:23:43,755
We both know it would go viral.

362
00:23:44,256 --> 00:23:46,007
It would be our biggest story.

363
00:23:46,091 --> 00:23:47,884
[Kaho] Sure, but at what cost?

364
00:23:47,968 --> 00:23:50,303
She's talking about killing people.

365
00:23:50,846 --> 00:23:52,973
Are you seriously okay with that?

366
00:23:54,850 --> 00:23:57,477
I said it before
and I'll say it again now.

367
00:23:59,896 --> 00:24:02,607
I'm perfectly fine
with the way things are.

368
00:24:03,275 --> 00:24:06,278
And yeah, that includes
doing videos with you that never go viral.

369
00:24:06,361 --> 00:24:07,904
I don't care about that.

370
00:24:08,822 --> 00:24:10,282
We do things our way.

371
00:24:10,782 --> 00:24:12,200
And it's really fun.

372
00:24:14,077 --> 00:24:16,621
I mean, you're right.
It's been fun until now, I guess.

373
00:24:17,122 --> 00:24:20,083
But imagine how much more fun
it would be if we made money.

374
00:24:21,084 --> 00:24:23,962
[groans] Money is all you care about.

375
00:24:29,092 --> 00:24:32,012
I guess
I just don't wanna be a nobody anymore.

376
00:24:33,722 --> 00:24:35,432
[Kaho] What's that supposed to mean?

377
00:24:35,515 --> 00:24:37,225
[Fujita exhales slowly]

378
00:24:37,309 --> 00:24:39,561
You're my brother, is that not enough?

379
00:24:40,061 --> 00:24:41,104
Guess not.

380
00:24:42,230 --> 00:24:43,940
That's what makes us different.

381
00:24:50,947 --> 00:24:53,116
That's not what I'm saying.

382
00:24:55,994 --> 00:24:56,995
Kaho,

383
00:24:58,580 --> 00:24:59,956
I just feel that

384
00:25:01,082 --> 00:25:02,792
you and I were chosen, you know?

385
00:25:04,836 --> 00:25:07,172
[Kaho] Oh, great, there you go again.

386
00:25:11,801 --> 00:25:13,053
[Fujita sighs]

387
00:25:13,136 --> 00:25:15,138
[soft, intriguing piano music playing]

388
00:25:18,934 --> 00:25:20,352
[Fujita grunts, then coughs]

389
00:25:20,435 --> 00:25:23,855
All right, well, I'm off
to my exciting part-time job.

390
00:25:32,864 --> 00:25:33,990
[Fujita] What's this?

391
00:25:34,658 --> 00:25:35,575
It's your present.

392
00:25:36,076 --> 00:25:37,536
For your birthday tomorrow.

393
00:25:38,995 --> 00:25:40,121
[Fujita] Seriously?

394
00:25:47,671 --> 00:25:48,713
Ah!

395
00:25:49,381 --> 00:25:50,507
[chuckles]

396
00:25:56,388 --> 00:25:58,682
[laughs]

397
00:25:58,765 --> 00:25:59,849
Kaho!

398
00:26:02,185 --> 00:26:05,146
You've always been there.
Come on, my sister.

399
00:26:06,022 --> 00:26:07,315
Don't be gross.

400
00:26:08,233 --> 00:26:10,735
[Kaho] Oh, if you see any unsold <i>bento</i>,
bring them back.

401
00:26:25,375 --> 00:26:27,377
[intriguing music building]

402
00:26:46,062 --> 00:26:48,064
[music fades out]

403
00:26:51,026 --> 00:26:52,068
Kenji.

404
00:26:55,572 --> 00:26:57,449
If all this turns out to be true…

405
00:27:00,201 --> 00:27:02,579
you think you'll be able
to arrest Sakamoto?

406
00:27:07,792 --> 00:27:10,629
I don't believe he'd ever do this, so…

407
00:27:15,050 --> 00:27:16,134
I'll meet him,

408
00:27:16,885 --> 00:27:18,094
and I'll find out.

409
00:27:20,388 --> 00:27:21,848
[Kenji exhales heavily]

410
00:27:25,644 --> 00:27:27,520
[chilling music rumbling]

411
00:27:37,364 --> 00:27:38,406
[knock at door]

412
00:27:39,199 --> 00:27:40,200
What is it?

413
00:27:41,284 --> 00:27:44,120
It's Kenji.
He said he's stopping by tonight.

414
00:27:44,746 --> 00:27:47,207
- What?
- Why? What's wrong?

415
00:27:49,084 --> 00:27:50,085
[sighs]

416
00:27:50,168 --> 00:27:52,629
Nothing. Sounds good.

417
00:27:54,297 --> 00:27:57,050
[Chieko] I'll set a place for him
at the table for dinner.

418
00:28:00,512 --> 00:28:03,473
["Ellie My Love"
by Southern All Stars playing]

419
00:28:07,268 --> 00:28:08,436
<i>♪ Ellie ♪</i>

420
00:28:08,978 --> 00:28:10,563
<i>♪ My love ♪</i>

421
00:28:10,647 --> 00:28:13,650
<i>♪ So sweet ♪</i>

422
00:28:14,234 --> 00:28:15,360
<i>♪ Ellie ♪</i>

423
00:28:15,860 --> 00:28:17,320
<i>♪ My love ♪</i>

424
00:28:17,404 --> 00:28:20,907
<i>♪ So sweet ♪</i>

425
00:28:28,164 --> 00:28:30,041
Greetings, listener.

426
00:28:30,625 --> 00:28:32,460
Go right ahead,

427
00:28:33,169 --> 00:28:35,630
and make a wish.

428
00:28:35,714 --> 00:28:37,924
[tense music playing]

429
00:28:49,018 --> 00:28:50,228
Uh, uh…

430
00:29:10,999 --> 00:29:13,209
[doorbell rings]

431
00:29:14,294 --> 00:29:15,879
[sighs heavily]

432
00:29:19,507 --> 00:29:23,011
- [Chieko chuckles] Kenji, good to see you!
- [Kenji] Thank you for having me.

433
00:29:23,094 --> 00:29:25,930
Please, we love it.
We wish you'd come over more often!

434
00:29:26,014 --> 00:29:28,433
It gets a little stale,
just two of us. Here.

435
00:29:28,516 --> 00:29:30,351
[Kyoko] I hope you don't mind if I join.

436
00:29:30,435 --> 00:29:33,271
- And who's that?
- Uh, this is…

437
00:29:35,732 --> 00:29:37,567
- [Chieko] Ah.
- [Kenji sighs]

438
00:29:37,650 --> 00:29:39,652
[footsteps approaching]

439
00:29:53,625 --> 00:29:55,835
GRADUATION CEREMONY

440
00:29:55,919 --> 00:29:58,546
[pages turning steadily]

441
00:30:30,328 --> 00:30:31,663
[Sakamoto sighs]

442
00:30:32,163 --> 00:30:36,751
So this Mufu, whatever it is,
included Otomo, head of the Syndicate,

443
00:30:36,835 --> 00:30:39,504
you, the Superintendent General,

444
00:30:40,046 --> 00:30:42,924
and then someone else named Kai.

445
00:30:43,007 --> 00:30:45,718
You were all listed
as the leaders of this thing.

446
00:30:47,178 --> 00:30:49,681
We know that the journal
belonged to Obata.

447
00:30:50,306 --> 00:30:53,601
He and everyone else who pushed back
against this were murdered.

448
00:30:54,102 --> 00:30:57,188
Mufu did that as well. Didn't they, sir?

449
00:30:58,064 --> 00:30:59,732
[Sakamoto breathes slowly]

450
00:31:00,567 --> 00:31:02,151
Tell me it's not true.

451
00:31:05,196 --> 00:31:06,197
It's not.

452
00:31:07,448 --> 00:31:08,366
Right?

453
00:31:13,997 --> 00:31:15,415
Everything

454
00:31:16,666 --> 00:31:18,334
was for the greater good.

455
00:31:19,252 --> 00:31:21,754
- The good of the country.
- [Kenji scoffs]

456
00:31:22,964 --> 00:31:23,965
What?

457
00:31:26,718 --> 00:31:30,305
The White Center people who died
during the meteorite cleanup…

458
00:31:35,226 --> 00:31:37,437
were chalked off as missing persons.

459
00:31:39,063 --> 00:31:40,189
[Kenji exhales slowly]

460
00:31:40,273 --> 00:31:42,275
[chilling music droning]

461
00:31:43,192 --> 00:31:45,778
Was that because the meteorite
wasn't safe?

462
00:31:47,155 --> 00:31:49,449
Yes. It was toxic.

463
00:31:51,075 --> 00:31:52,410
Even deadly.

464
00:31:54,454 --> 00:31:57,040
So all those people called "human fuel,"

465
00:31:57,624 --> 00:31:59,417
who died on your orders,

466
00:32:01,044 --> 00:32:03,713
were all expendable
for the good of the country?

467
00:32:06,382 --> 00:32:09,802
[Sakamoto] Why don't you talk about
the lives we <i>did </i>save with that decision?

468
00:32:09,886 --> 00:32:10,929
200,000 people!

469
00:32:11,012 --> 00:32:12,847
If we had let the damage
from the meteor spread,

470
00:32:12,931 --> 00:32:14,849
it would've reached the children's expo.

471
00:32:14,933 --> 00:32:17,936
I'm sorry,
but it was the only possible choice!

472
00:32:22,774 --> 00:32:23,858
Is that…

473
00:32:27,320 --> 00:32:28,905
really how you feel?

474
00:32:29,572 --> 00:32:31,908
Or is that what you tell yourself?

475
00:32:44,295 --> 00:32:45,546
[Kyoko] "Ren Tsutsumida."

476
00:32:45,630 --> 00:32:47,465
"Mobilized to meteorite disposal team."

477
00:32:47,548 --> 00:32:49,676
"Participated in
environmental cleanup work."

478
00:32:49,759 --> 00:32:51,344
"Processed as missing."

479
00:32:54,305 --> 00:32:56,182
Do you know who this man is?

480
00:33:00,478 --> 00:33:02,897
REN TSUTSUMIDA

481
00:33:03,898 --> 00:33:05,316
You do, don't you?

482
00:33:06,234 --> 00:33:07,360
The Human Vapor.

483
00:33:07,443 --> 00:33:08,987
[Sakamoto breathes shakily]

484
00:33:09,904 --> 00:33:11,322
I would bet

485
00:33:12,448 --> 00:33:13,992
you're his next victim.

486
00:33:19,080 --> 00:33:20,915
So you may as well tell us

487
00:33:21,666 --> 00:33:23,960
who this mysterious Kai person is.

488
00:33:28,214 --> 00:33:29,966
[Sakamoto breathes shakily]

489
00:33:33,678 --> 00:33:34,887
[Sakamoto] I'm sorry.

490
00:33:44,814 --> 00:33:45,982
I can't.

491
00:33:54,532 --> 00:33:55,533
Let's go.

492
00:33:56,534 --> 00:33:58,286
We got what we came for.

493
00:34:00,997 --> 00:34:01,914
[sighs]

494
00:34:05,334 --> 00:34:06,836
I appreciate…

495
00:34:09,630 --> 00:34:11,382
everything you've done for me.

496
00:34:14,844 --> 00:34:16,929
- Oh.
- [Kenji] I'm sorry. Excuse us.

497
00:34:17,013 --> 00:34:18,014
[Chieko] Wait, what?

498
00:34:18,723 --> 00:34:19,557
Oh.

499
00:34:20,099 --> 00:34:21,684
You're not staying for dinner?

500
00:34:26,898 --> 00:34:27,899
[lighter strikes]

501
00:34:31,944 --> 00:34:33,863
THE HUMAN VAPOR
EXCLUSIVE VIDEO OBTAINED!

502
00:34:33,946 --> 00:34:35,323
WHO'S THE NEXT TARGET?

503
00:34:35,406 --> 00:34:37,408
[mysterious music playing]

504
00:34:51,589 --> 00:34:52,673
UPLOAD

505
00:34:53,174 --> 00:34:58,012
UPLOADING

506
00:34:58,096 --> 00:35:00,890
UPLOAD COMPLETE

507
00:35:08,356 --> 00:35:10,900
[Human Vapor] <i>To everyone</i>
<i>out there listening,</i>

508
00:35:11,692 --> 00:35:13,444
<i>the next target is</i>

509
00:35:13,528 --> 00:35:16,280
<i>Superintendent General Sakamoto.</i>

510
00:35:17,156 --> 00:35:19,992
<i>I will kill you tomorrow at noon.</i>

511
00:35:20,076 --> 00:35:21,452
<i>You have been warned.</i>

512
00:35:21,536 --> 00:35:22,787
WHO'S THE NEXT TARGET?

513
00:35:22,870 --> 00:35:26,624
<i>There is, however,</i>
<i>one way you can survive.</i>

514
00:35:27,959 --> 00:35:30,086
<i>Publicly confess your crimes</i>

515
00:35:30,169 --> 00:35:33,131
<i>and reveal the names</i>
<i>of all your coconspirators</i>

516
00:35:33,214 --> 00:35:35,383
<i>involved with White Center.</i>

517
00:35:35,883 --> 00:35:39,053
<i>You must face the music,</i>
<i>Superintendent General.</i>

518
00:35:39,554 --> 00:35:41,514
<i>Do this by noon tomorrow.</i>

519
00:35:42,056 --> 00:35:45,143
<i>If you fail to make</i>
<i>this public announcement,</i>

520
00:35:45,226 --> 00:35:48,771
<i>then you will meet the same fate</i>
<i>as Kyugo Sano</i>

521
00:35:49,272 --> 00:35:51,315
<i>and Saburo Otomo.</i>

522
00:35:51,816 --> 00:35:54,569
<i>You'd better not test me on this.</i>

523
00:35:54,652 --> 00:35:56,279
[Sakamoto breathes shakily]

524
00:35:56,362 --> 00:35:58,573
<i>Do the right thing.</i>

525
00:35:59,198 --> 00:36:02,952
<i>Hold the press conference. Confess.</i>

526
00:36:08,583 --> 00:36:10,084
[pins clattering]

527
00:36:10,168 --> 00:36:11,085
[tuts]

528
00:36:11,169 --> 00:36:13,588
[tense electronic music playing]

529
00:36:21,053 --> 00:36:22,680
This is from Kai.

530
00:36:30,605 --> 00:36:32,148
[Yoshida inhales sharply]

531
00:36:32,648 --> 00:36:34,108
You know…

532
00:36:36,736 --> 00:36:39,197
there's something I need to ask.

533
00:36:46,245 --> 00:36:47,622
My old man,

534
00:36:49,290 --> 00:36:51,459
he really loved bowling.

535
00:36:54,420 --> 00:36:57,381
We would come here a lot back in the day.

536
00:37:06,807 --> 00:37:09,769
You lost someone very dear to you,
didn't you?

537
00:37:09,852 --> 00:37:13,397
Be honest.
You took out Yamazaki yourself, right?

538
00:37:13,481 --> 00:37:15,441
[Yoshida chuckles awkwardly]

539
00:37:15,942 --> 00:37:18,903
No, that wasn't me.
Let's all just breathe, huh?

540
00:37:35,628 --> 00:37:37,546
[clasps locking]

541
00:37:45,721 --> 00:37:47,139
Snake eyes.

542
00:37:48,349 --> 00:37:50,101
If you get those pins, I'll do it.

543
00:38:02,446 --> 00:38:03,447
[Yoshida] Hmm.

544
00:38:07,326 --> 00:38:09,787
[grunts] You'll regret that.

545
00:38:10,871 --> 00:38:12,873
But you got yourself a deal.

546
00:38:14,583 --> 00:38:16,836
Or I can kill you now.

547
00:38:17,461 --> 00:38:19,422
[Yoshida chuckles]

548
00:38:22,883 --> 00:38:24,802
You ever heard of the Hydra? Huh?

549
00:38:25,303 --> 00:38:28,222
It's from Greek mythology.
Cut off one head, two grow back.

550
00:38:28,306 --> 00:38:30,141
Kinda like this organization.

551
00:38:31,434 --> 00:38:35,104
You don't collapse when you lose the head.

552
00:38:35,187 --> 00:38:38,524
You adapt, grow two heads.
Become stronger.

553
00:38:38,607 --> 00:38:41,027
Thanks for the lesson.
Now shut up and bowl.

554
00:38:46,657 --> 00:38:48,826
[pulsing synth-pop playing]

555
00:39:40,252 --> 00:39:42,254
[music fades]

556
00:39:48,010 --> 00:39:50,012
[pulsing synth-pop resumes]

557
00:40:09,156 --> 00:40:10,074
[music ends]

558
00:40:10,157 --> 00:40:12,326
So yeah. The one here.

559
00:40:13,744 --> 00:40:15,955
I'll leave it to you to work out the rest.

560
00:40:26,465 --> 00:40:27,466
What do we do?

561
00:40:37,476 --> 00:40:38,436
Kyoko.

562
00:40:44,024 --> 00:40:44,900
Uh…

563
00:40:48,237 --> 00:40:49,947
Could you maybe…

564
00:40:54,285 --> 00:40:55,995
wait before going public?

565
00:41:02,585 --> 00:41:03,752
[Kyoko sighs]

566
00:41:03,836 --> 00:41:04,962
I think…

567
00:41:07,965 --> 00:41:10,759
everything in the journal
is probably true.

568
00:41:17,516 --> 00:41:19,768
You could tell from the look on his face.

569
00:41:25,107 --> 00:41:26,984
I've never seen him like that.

570
00:41:37,203 --> 00:41:38,579
[Kenji sighs heavily]

571
00:41:44,585 --> 00:41:46,378
He's my family, Kyoko.

572
00:41:47,671 --> 00:41:48,672
But…

573
00:41:48,756 --> 00:41:50,758
[tender piano music playing]

574
00:41:52,801 --> 00:41:55,304
…I'll make sure he and this Kai…

575
00:41:57,848 --> 00:42:00,684
are brought to justice
for everything they've done.

576
00:42:04,647 --> 00:42:05,648
I…

577
00:42:13,489 --> 00:42:15,324
just need you to…

578
00:42:16,867 --> 00:42:18,661
forget about the journal.

579
00:42:34,218 --> 00:42:35,553
[Kyoko sighs softly]

580
00:42:36,887 --> 00:42:37,930
Kenji.

581
00:42:45,020 --> 00:42:46,188
There's something…

582
00:42:54,405 --> 00:42:55,489
Never mind.

583
00:42:56,574 --> 00:42:58,367
- Thank you.
- Course.

584
00:42:58,450 --> 00:42:59,326
Yeah.

585
00:43:02,037 --> 00:43:03,330
- [Kenji] See you later.
- Bye.

586
00:43:03,414 --> 00:43:04,331
[Kenji] Goodnight.

587
00:43:14,675 --> 00:43:17,428
[phone vibrating]

588
00:43:22,600 --> 00:43:24,602
[music fades out]

589
00:43:25,185 --> 00:43:26,145
Kenji.

590
00:43:29,148 --> 00:43:31,066
I think I've made my decision.

591
00:43:35,154 --> 00:43:36,739
I'll go to the press,

592
00:43:37,615 --> 00:43:39,617
and I'll tell them all of it.

593
00:43:43,579 --> 00:43:45,039
Uh, okay.

594
00:43:46,624 --> 00:43:48,584
[Sakamoto] <i>I'll tell them all about Kai</i>

595
00:43:50,294 --> 00:43:52,338
<i>and the terrible things I've done.</i>

596
00:43:54,256 --> 00:43:55,215
<i>Kenji…</i>

597
00:43:56,342 --> 00:43:58,677
there's something else you should know.

598
00:44:01,263 --> 00:44:02,556
Your father…

599
00:44:06,060 --> 00:44:08,187
I'm responsible for his death.

600
00:44:10,189 --> 00:44:12,191
[somber music playing]

601
00:44:14,485 --> 00:44:15,736
What do you mean?

602
00:44:15,819 --> 00:44:19,657
[Sakamoto] <i>I'm sorry. I really am.</i>
<i>I hope you can believe me.</i>

603
00:44:20,366 --> 00:44:22,451
<i>But I just wanted you to hear it from me.</i>

604
00:44:22,951 --> 00:44:24,495
<i>Before it's too late.</i>

605
00:44:24,578 --> 00:44:26,288
[scoffs] Uh, what are you--

606
00:44:26,372 --> 00:44:27,665
[Sakamoto] <i>I'm sorry.</i>

607
00:44:29,166 --> 00:44:30,250
What are you saying?

608
00:44:30,334 --> 00:44:32,002
- [call disconnects]
- Hello?

609
00:44:33,712 --> 00:44:34,713
[sighs]

610
00:44:34,797 --> 00:44:36,757
[music fades out]

611
00:44:36,840 --> 00:44:39,385
[phone vibrating]

612
00:44:42,554 --> 00:44:43,555
[Kyoko] Hello?

613
00:44:43,639 --> 00:44:45,766
Kono, get your ass back here right away.

614
00:44:45,849 --> 00:44:48,352
I just got word
from the Superintendent General.

615
00:44:48,435 --> 00:44:50,688
He's holding some
emergency press conference here.

616
00:44:50,771 --> 00:44:52,272
If I were you, I'd get back.

617
00:44:52,356 --> 00:44:54,858
- What?
<i>- He said something about coming clean.</i>

618
00:44:54,942 --> 00:44:57,277
Okay, thank you. I'll be right there.

619
00:44:57,361 --> 00:44:59,363
[intense music playing]

620
00:45:06,787 --> 00:45:08,789
[deodorant spray hissing]

621
00:45:08,872 --> 00:45:10,541
[intense music continues]

622
00:45:27,641 --> 00:45:29,518
[music ends]

623
00:45:30,102 --> 00:45:32,062
[Sakamoto] Yoshida, I didn't expect…

624
00:45:33,272 --> 00:45:35,816
I'm sorry, but I was worried.

625
00:45:36,984 --> 00:45:38,026
You were.

626
00:45:39,611 --> 00:45:41,864
[Yoshida] Are you sure you wanna do this?

627
00:45:46,452 --> 00:45:48,370
Yes, I'm ready. It's time.

628
00:45:52,458 --> 00:45:53,751
If you say so.

629
00:45:54,918 --> 00:45:56,795
Then I'm gonna stand by your side,

630
00:45:56,879 --> 00:45:58,630
whatever punishment may come.

631
00:46:01,967 --> 00:46:03,051
I'll drive you.

632
00:46:12,227 --> 00:46:13,687
[car doors unlocking]

633
00:46:22,654 --> 00:46:25,699
[newscaster] <i>In response to the video,</i>
<i>in which the Human Vapor announced</i>

634
00:46:25,783 --> 00:46:28,577
<i>that he would kill</i>
<i>the Superintendent General, we're hearing…</i>

635
00:46:28,660 --> 00:46:31,622
- This thing's got 1.5 million views.
- Jesus, really?

636
00:46:31,705 --> 00:46:32,915
- Kyoko.
- Hey guys.

637
00:46:32,998 --> 00:46:35,042
[newscaster] <i>The video was posted by…</i>

638
00:46:35,125 --> 00:46:37,753
All the networks are scrambling
because of that stupid video.

639
00:46:37,836 --> 00:46:40,798
I'll bet they're camped outside
the Superintendent's house now.

640
00:46:40,881 --> 00:46:43,550
[newscaster] <i>It's made waves online</i>
<i>and on social media…</i>

641
00:46:43,634 --> 00:46:44,468
- Hey, Kyoko.
- Hi.

642
00:46:44,551 --> 00:46:47,054
[newscaster] <i>…having been viewed</i>
<i>1.5 million times.</i>

643
00:46:47,137 --> 00:46:50,891
<i>There is, however,</i>
<i>one way you can survive.</i>

644
00:46:51,433 --> 00:46:53,352
<i>Publicly confess your crimes,</i>

645
00:46:54,102 --> 00:46:57,147
<i>and reveal the names</i>
<i>of all your co-conspirators</i>

646
00:46:57,231 --> 00:46:59,525
<i>involved with White Center.</i>

647
00:47:00,400 --> 00:47:03,153
<i>You must face the music,</i>
<i>Superintendent General.</i>

648
00:47:04,238 --> 00:47:06,490
<i>That is the only way.</i>

649
00:47:06,573 --> 00:47:10,744
[newscaster] <i>In the video,</i>
<i>he speaks directly to Sakamoto</i>

650
00:47:10,828 --> 00:47:12,871
<i>and claims the only way</i>
<i>he will spare his life</i>

651
00:47:12,955 --> 00:47:16,792
<i>is if Mr. Sakamoto reveals the nature</i>
<i>of his crimes, and the names of…</i>

652
00:47:16,875 --> 00:47:18,085
KAHO, TERROR ZONE

653
00:47:18,919 --> 00:47:21,588
<i>The man claims the General</i>
<i>has until noon tomorrow.</i>

654
00:47:21,672 --> 00:47:23,715
<i>No other information</i>
<i>is given in the video…</i>

655
00:47:23,799 --> 00:47:25,509
[phone rings out]

656
00:47:25,592 --> 00:47:27,719
<i>In response,</i>
<i>the Metropolitan Police Department</i>

657
00:47:27,803 --> 00:47:31,139
<i>has decided to strengthen security</i>
<i>around the Superintendent.</i>

658
00:47:31,223 --> 00:47:34,268
<i>This is the newest twist</i>
<i>in this incredible and frightening story.</i>

659
00:47:35,853 --> 00:47:37,062
[softly] Regarding

660
00:47:38,230 --> 00:47:39,690
the allegations…

661
00:47:51,910 --> 00:47:54,329
We're here, Superintendent.

662
00:47:59,585 --> 00:48:01,295
What are you talking about?

663
00:48:02,087 --> 00:48:02,963
This isn't…

664
00:48:17,185 --> 00:48:19,646
[reporter 1] I spoke to his wife.
He left a while ago.

665
00:48:19,730 --> 00:48:21,607
It doesn't make sense. He should be here.

666
00:48:21,690 --> 00:48:24,234
[director] Hmm.
You can't get in touch with him?

667
00:48:24,318 --> 00:48:27,863
[reporter 2] I've been trying
for the last hour. He's not answering.

668
00:48:28,655 --> 00:48:32,409
[director groans] Maybe he's spooked.
Doesn't make sense.

669
00:48:32,910 --> 00:48:34,328
[panting] Su…

670
00:48:34,828 --> 00:48:37,539
The Superintendent General… [panting]

671
00:48:37,623 --> 00:48:39,917
…was found dead in the backseat of a car.

672
00:48:40,626 --> 00:48:43,462
The police think… he committed suicide.

673
00:48:43,545 --> 00:48:46,715
- [reporter 3] Bullshit. There's no way.
- [director] Where was the car?

674
00:48:46,798 --> 00:48:49,092
[Tatsuya] Uh… some street in Minato Ward.

675
00:48:49,176 --> 00:48:51,094
[officer] Please, stop, sir! Stop!

676
00:48:52,429 --> 00:48:54,431
[tense, sinister music playing]

677
00:48:55,098 --> 00:48:56,308
[Motoyama] He's over there.

678
00:48:57,935 --> 00:48:59,436
[panting]

679
00:49:44,606 --> 00:49:45,440
[exhales]

680
00:49:46,733 --> 00:49:47,651
[sighs]

681
00:49:47,734 --> 00:49:49,820
[sinister music intensifies]

682
00:49:51,905 --> 00:49:53,907
[music continues]

683
00:50:07,421 --> 00:50:11,049
<i>Superintendent General Sakamoto</i>
<i>of the Metropolitan Police Department</i>

684
00:50:11,133 --> 00:50:14,886
<i>has been found dead in a car</i>
<i>parked on a street in Minato Ward.</i>

685
00:50:14,970 --> 00:50:17,097
<i>This comes after a public death threat</i>

686
00:50:17,180 --> 00:50:20,809
<i>from the man known as the Human Vapor</i>
<i>an hour ago.</i>

687
00:50:20,892 --> 00:50:22,436
<i>For those of you just joining us,</i>

688
00:50:22,519 --> 00:50:26,898
<i>we've received word that the dead body</i>
<i>of Superintendent General Sakamoto</i>

689
00:50:26,982 --> 00:50:28,567
<i>was found in a car parked on…</i>

690
00:50:28,650 --> 00:50:30,027
[speech fades]

691
00:50:41,663 --> 00:50:44,166
[wind blowing]

692
00:50:49,129 --> 00:50:51,131
[suspenseful music playing]

693
00:50:59,556 --> 00:51:02,184
[phone vibrating]

694
00:51:05,604 --> 00:51:07,606
[phone ringing out]

695
00:51:08,523 --> 00:51:09,858
[phone continues vibrating]

696
00:51:09,941 --> 00:51:11,818
[metallic rattling outside]

697
00:51:14,780 --> 00:51:15,906
Fujita?

698
00:51:15,989 --> 00:51:17,074
[toilet flushing]

699
00:51:17,157 --> 00:51:18,867
I didn't hear you come in.

700
00:51:22,162 --> 00:51:24,414
- [grunting]
- [Kaho gasps]

701
00:51:24,498 --> 00:51:26,666
[Riki] Sorry, it was an emergency. Also,

702
00:51:26,750 --> 00:51:28,668
you better restock!

703
00:51:29,628 --> 00:51:30,545
[man shouts] Hey!

704
00:51:30,629 --> 00:51:32,172
[tense music playing]

705
00:51:46,228 --> 00:51:48,855
[dramatic music playing]
